WEBVTT

00:15.348 --> 00:17.350
[dramatic music playing]

00:21.021 --> 00:24.399
[metal shinking]

00:34.242 --> 00:35.577
[horse neighing]

00:39.622 --> 00:40.623
Give the order.

00:41.207 --> 00:42.876
I'll give it when I'm ready.

00:42.959 --> 00:45.378
[music builds]

00:50.008 --> 00:52.260
[horse neighing]

00:52.343 --> 00:53.344
Game on.

00:56.097 --> 00:57.557
[music climaxes]

00:59.642 --> 01:00.685
[horse nickering]

01:01.436 --> 01:02.353
[Last Man 1] Keep up.

01:04.022 --> 01:06.441
[leaves rustling]

01:07.275 --> 01:08.526
[gun cocking]

01:09.360 --> 01:12.072
-[arrow whooshing]
-[horse squealing]

01:12.155 --> 01:14.407
[suspenseful music playing]

01:17.410 --> 01:19.454
-[gunshot]
-[horse neighing]

01:19.537 --> 01:21.289
Ambush!

01:21.372 --> 01:23.374
[gunshots]

01:25.251 --> 01:26.878
-Stay down.
-[gun cocking]

01:26.961 --> 01:29.756
[leaves rustling]

01:29.839 --> 01:32.258
[tense music playing]

01:32.342 --> 01:33.426
[leaves rustling]

01:33.510 --> 01:34.594
I can't see them.

01:35.804 --> 01:38.014
-[leaves rustling]
-Ah!

01:38.098 --> 01:40.767
-[sword shinking]
-Ah!

01:40.850 --> 01:42.519
-[slashing]
-[Last Man 2 grunts]

01:42.602 --> 01:44.354
-[knife shinking]
-[body clattering]

01:44.437 --> 01:46.189
You gotta be shittin' me.

01:49.901 --> 01:51.694
Contained! Move in.

01:57.742 --> 01:59.285
[panting]

02:01.496 --> 02:04.791
We're not going to hurt you.
We're here to set you free, Gus.

02:05.458 --> 02:07.544
Uh, thanks. What do I do now?

02:07.627 --> 02:09.129
Hey, he can talk.

02:09.212 --> 02:12.382
Yeah, but why isn't he running off
like all the other hybrids?

02:12.465 --> 02:15.176
Clearly, he's not like
all the other hybrids, Pony.

02:15.969 --> 02:18.346
We've been here too long.
We need to move.

02:19.389 --> 02:21.850
Gus, we're offering you your freedom.

02:21.933 --> 02:24.435
You can go wherever you want,
just make it far from him.

02:24.519 --> 02:27.730
Good luck with that. I've been
trying to get rid of him for days.

02:28.648 --> 02:30.108
-[taser buzzing]
-[Jepperd grunts]

02:31.609 --> 02:34.070
-Why is he still alive?
-He was tied up along with Gus.

02:34.154 --> 02:37.323
Besides, I thought you always
needed to give the command.

02:37.407 --> 02:39.033
[suspenseful music playing]

02:43.288 --> 02:44.289
Shoot him.

02:44.372 --> 02:46.374
-No, don't! No! Don't!
-[gun cocking]

02:46.457 --> 02:48.793
[somber music playing]

02:58.928 --> 03:00.388
Take them both back.

03:00.471 --> 03:01.306
Both?

03:03.349 --> 03:04.976
We've never spared anybody before.

03:05.059 --> 03:07.979
And we've never rescued
a talking hybrid, either.

03:10.148 --> 03:12.150
Delta procedures. River route.

03:12.233 --> 03:13.067
Roll out.

03:18.156 --> 03:19.824
[muttering]

03:21.242 --> 03:24.829
[journey music playing]

03:32.045 --> 03:34.547
[narrator exhales] Sweet solitude.

03:35.340 --> 03:37.759
That's all Aimee Eden thought she wanted.

03:37.842 --> 03:39.719
[man over radio]
The Last Men burned the crops.

03:39.802 --> 03:42.347
We're in Montrose,
in the old Quaker meeting house.

03:42.430 --> 03:44.641
Is anyone there? Can you hear me?

03:44.724 --> 03:46.768
[narrator]
But that was before she met someone

03:46.851 --> 03:49.771
worth more than
all the solitude in the world.

03:49.854 --> 03:50.772
[girl] Mom?

03:51.356 --> 03:52.815
Why aren't there any more men?

03:53.566 --> 03:54.484
What?

03:55.151 --> 03:56.569
The man on the radio,

03:57.320 --> 03:59.697
he was scared by the Last Men.

04:00.615 --> 04:02.325
Why are they the last ones?

04:02.408 --> 04:03.409
Just a name.

04:05.328 --> 04:06.996
Silly name for silly people.

04:08.122 --> 04:11.876
You're supposed to be asleep, and you're
not supposed to be listening to this.

04:14.545 --> 04:17.006
Since you're already up and about,
might as well go get ready.

04:18.341 --> 04:19.384
We're going shopping.

04:19.467 --> 04:20.510
[squeals]

04:20.593 --> 04:22.428
[light piano music playing]

04:27.392 --> 04:28.893
[giggling]

04:51.874 --> 04:53.626
-[girl giggling]
-[Aimee] Wait for me!

04:56.754 --> 04:59.257
-[Aimee] Is it heavy yet?
-[girl] Yeah, all of a sudden.

04:59.340 --> 05:01.676
[both laughing]

05:06.639 --> 05:07.807
[girl chuckles]

05:27.410 --> 05:28.244
Mom?

05:29.412 --> 05:31.372
-What's wrong, Pigtail?
-I smell smoke.

05:33.249 --> 05:36.252
[ominous music playing]

05:45.887 --> 05:47.096
[Aimee inhales sharply]

05:47.180 --> 05:49.182
[footsteps approaching]

06:02.195 --> 06:03.488
[gun cocking]

06:07.575 --> 06:08.409
[radio beeping]

06:08.493 --> 06:10.370
[man on radio] Patrol, report to base.

06:11.496 --> 06:13.289
Copy that. En route.

06:13.373 --> 06:14.457
[radio beeping]

06:21.923 --> 06:24.092
[chains rattling]

06:29.514 --> 06:30.473
[doors slam]

06:33.434 --> 06:36.062
I'm glad there aren't that many men left.

06:36.646 --> 06:37.480
Me too.

06:51.327 --> 06:54.080
[journey music playing]

07:03.214 --> 07:04.215
[Gus] What is this place?

07:05.716 --> 07:07.093
This is our home.

07:15.726 --> 07:18.563
[ethereal music playing]

07:18.646 --> 07:20.064
[door slams]

07:37.415 --> 07:40.001
-[animals sounds echoing]
-[gasps]

07:42.211 --> 07:44.422
Every time someone gets
initiated into the Army,

07:44.505 --> 07:46.007
they paint their favorite animal.

07:49.760 --> 07:51.053
Is that one yours?

07:51.721 --> 07:52.597
[Bear] Yeah.

07:54.182 --> 07:55.766
Why aren't there any more after it?

07:55.850 --> 07:58.269
I was the very first member
of the Animal Army…

08:00.313 --> 08:01.939
because I created it.

08:05.943 --> 08:07.737
Wait, where'd Jepp go?

08:08.613 --> 08:10.490
You're not gonna hurt him still, are you?

08:10.573 --> 08:13.117
No one does anything here
without my permission.

08:14.118 --> 08:15.119
I promise.

08:15.661 --> 08:18.539
I cross my heart and hope to die.

08:18.623 --> 08:20.249
I don't want you to die.

08:20.333 --> 08:21.334
Don't worry.

08:22.418 --> 08:24.712
It just means an extra-strong promise.

08:24.795 --> 08:27.381
["Hey There Cowgirl"
by Palm Springsteen playing]

08:28.090 --> 08:29.008
[snickers]

08:29.550 --> 08:30.426
Now,

08:31.344 --> 08:34.138
you ready to go
to the best place on Earth?

08:43.648 --> 08:45.066
[soldier 1] Check it out. It's Bear.

08:45.691 --> 08:47.485
[soldier 2] Everyone, Bear's back.

08:47.568 --> 08:48.611
[soldier 3] Check it out.

08:49.070 --> 08:50.571
[soldier 4] Guys, the buck.

08:51.572 --> 08:53.074
He's here.

08:53.157 --> 08:55.034
[indistinct chatter]

08:55.117 --> 08:56.702
Why are they all staring?

08:58.120 --> 09:00.373
They've never met
a hybrid as special as you,

09:00.915 --> 09:02.625
so they're a little excited.

09:03.751 --> 09:05.044
[soldier 5] Yeah, that's crazy.

09:05.628 --> 09:07.380
Where are all the parents?

09:07.463 --> 09:09.090
We don't have any.

09:09.173 --> 09:10.341
No parents?

09:11.050 --> 09:13.511
Don't worry,
they won't be so weird in a second.

09:13.594 --> 09:15.930
Just say hi.

09:23.229 --> 09:24.063
Hi.

09:24.146 --> 09:27.775
[crowd clamoring]

09:28.526 --> 09:30.736
[soldier 6] Oh, man,
can I touch it? Is that cool?

09:30.820 --> 09:32.321
[clamoring continues]

09:32.405 --> 09:34.282
[Bear shushing]

09:36.075 --> 09:37.952
Gus is king for the night.

09:38.035 --> 09:40.037
[crowd cheering]

09:44.959 --> 09:46.836
[slurping]

09:47.545 --> 09:48.671
Do you like candy?

09:48.754 --> 09:52.049
My Pubba let me have syrup,
but he said it would rot my teeth.

09:54.135 --> 09:55.136
It's worth it.

09:55.678 --> 09:57.722
These are my favorite.

10:04.020 --> 10:06.397
These taste like lightning!
What are these?

10:06.480 --> 10:08.107
-[scattered laughter]
-They're sour gummies.

10:09.483 --> 10:10.943
[computers beeping]

10:11.027 --> 10:12.987
Why do you have shiny boxes?

10:14.196 --> 10:15.781
You've never seen a computer?

10:16.949 --> 10:19.410
You want to see
what's inside the shiny boxes?

10:19.493 --> 10:20.411
Yeah.

10:21.329 --> 10:22.246
I'll be right back.

10:26.751 --> 10:29.629
-What's in them?
-The whole world's in here, man.

10:29.712 --> 10:31.964
[keyboard clacking]

10:32.048 --> 10:35.301
[video game noises]

10:35.384 --> 10:36.802
-[keyboard clacking]
-[beeping]

10:36.886 --> 10:38.220
Ready? Watch this.

10:39.930 --> 10:41.223
[Rhino] And look!

10:43.017 --> 10:43.976
I get to be you.

10:44.769 --> 10:46.520
Why would you want that?

10:48.439 --> 10:51.025
What do you mean?
We all wish we could be like you.

10:52.485 --> 10:56.405
Well, my friend Rusty said
that most people hate kids like me,

10:56.489 --> 10:58.032
'cause we caused the Sick.

10:58.532 --> 10:59.825
Most people are dumb.

11:01.369 --> 11:03.204
Hybrids didn't cause the virus.

11:03.287 --> 11:04.163
Really?

11:05.247 --> 11:06.207
Then who did?

11:06.791 --> 11:07.750
No one knows.

11:08.334 --> 11:09.460
But it wasn't you.

11:10.503 --> 11:13.339
Hybrids are how the Earth survives.

11:14.632 --> 11:15.466
Look.

11:17.426 --> 11:20.096
Before the virus, Earth was dying.

11:20.179 --> 11:21.013
Humans…

11:21.972 --> 11:23.099
Grownups,

11:23.182 --> 11:26.268
had ruined it,
all for their own selfish needs,

11:26.852 --> 11:28.312
leaving us with nothing.

11:29.563 --> 11:32.983
My Pubba said the bad people
took everything they wanted.

11:33.484 --> 11:34.318
Yeah.

11:35.486 --> 11:36.320
They did.

11:37.321 --> 11:38.280
They still do.

11:39.532 --> 11:40.783
[melancholic music playing]

11:40.866 --> 11:44.036
Did you know that before the virus came,
the water wasn't blue?

11:44.829 --> 11:47.540
That's because
they filled the water with trash.

11:48.082 --> 11:49.125
The sky too.

11:51.460 --> 11:53.629
But once kids like you were born,

11:54.130 --> 11:56.173
the Earth could start to heal.

11:57.591 --> 11:59.635
You can live without taking.

11:59.719 --> 12:01.429
You can keep the Earth alive.

12:02.012 --> 12:04.181
And that's why we vowed

12:04.265 --> 12:07.059
to always protect hybrids,
no matter what the cost.

12:07.143 --> 12:09.019
-[soldier 2] That's right.
-[soldier 3] Always.

12:10.980 --> 12:13.482
Is that why no grownups live here?

12:14.316 --> 12:16.068
[rhythmic music playing]

12:16.152 --> 12:19.530
My entire family was slaughtered
in cold blood by grownups.

12:20.322 --> 12:21.574
By Last Men.

12:22.742 --> 12:25.661
And that's 'cause
they had no one to protect them.

12:27.705 --> 12:28.581
But now,

12:29.749 --> 12:31.250
we can protect ourselves.

12:33.043 --> 12:37.214
I have one last
very important question for you, Gus.

12:39.759 --> 12:41.177
Do you know how to drive?

12:41.677 --> 12:43.763
-[rhythmic music intensifies]
-[horn honking]

12:49.602 --> 12:50.644
[soldier] Watch out!

12:53.522 --> 12:56.150
I'm not sure how much longer
we can hold him.

12:57.318 --> 12:58.944
You've seen how big he is, right?

12:59.028 --> 13:00.362
We've dealt with worse.

13:01.238 --> 13:03.324
I don't get
why we can't just kill him now.

13:03.407 --> 13:04.950
I've got Daisy all ready to go.

13:05.034 --> 13:06.160
[Bear] This is different.

13:06.243 --> 13:08.871
We've never had a hybrid
protect their poacher before.

13:10.498 --> 13:11.707
Aren't you curious why?

13:11.791 --> 13:12.625
No!

13:13.584 --> 13:15.252
And you shouldn't be either.

13:16.086 --> 13:17.463
He has the brand.

13:18.714 --> 13:20.674
Do I need to remind you who's in charge?

13:39.860 --> 13:41.862
[Looney Tunes theme song playing]

13:54.625 --> 13:57.253
Pubba could have made
hundreds of books here.

13:59.171 --> 14:00.631
What's your book gonna be about?

14:02.591 --> 14:04.844
My adventures with Jepp, to find my mom.

14:06.720 --> 14:08.138
You're trying to find your mom?

14:09.557 --> 14:10.850
Yeah. Is that okay?

14:14.311 --> 14:17.398
Jepp's taking me to Colorado
because that's where she is.

14:17.481 --> 14:19.149
Do you know her? Her name is Birdie.

14:19.942 --> 14:20.776
Birdie?

14:22.528 --> 14:24.446
What a fitting name for your mom.

14:25.406 --> 14:27.324
Sorry, I don't know her.

14:30.744 --> 14:32.830
But we can maybe find out more.

14:34.206 --> 14:35.040
We can?

14:37.793 --> 14:40.212
[whispering] Let's keep this a secret
between you and me, okay?

14:44.884 --> 14:47.219
Find out everything you can,
Birdie in Colorado.

14:51.140 --> 14:52.766
Is it like this here all the time?

14:54.435 --> 14:55.561
Would you like to stay?

14:57.563 --> 15:01.442
Well, maybe I can come back and visit
after Jepp and I find my mom.

15:04.278 --> 15:05.487
Can I ask you something?

15:07.156 --> 15:09.158
If Jepp was supposed
to take you to Colorado,

15:09.241 --> 15:11.076
why aren't you there right now?

15:11.160 --> 15:14.538
Because we got caught
by the bad men, remember?

15:14.622 --> 15:16.040
Before you guys came.

15:18.459 --> 15:20.753
Was Jepp upset
that you guys missed the train?

15:21.629 --> 15:23.589
Well, he wasn't coming with.

15:23.672 --> 15:24.673
It was just me.

15:25.341 --> 15:28.177
So you were gonna
have to go on the train alone?

15:28.260 --> 15:29.094
[Gus] Yeah.

15:30.554 --> 15:32.097
Seems kind of scary.

15:32.681 --> 15:34.725
Yeah, but I've been alone before.

15:35.267 --> 15:36.936
After Pubba got the Sick.

15:37.519 --> 15:38.437
I can do it.

15:39.563 --> 15:41.023
How long were you alone for?

15:41.815 --> 15:42.942
I don't know.

15:43.025 --> 15:44.485
All the seasons.

15:45.819 --> 15:47.279
That's a long time.

15:47.363 --> 15:48.280
Yeah.

15:48.864 --> 15:50.866
[ominous music playing]

16:00.918 --> 16:03.295
When I lost my family, I was alone too.

16:05.047 --> 16:06.256
I was pretty scared.

16:07.091 --> 16:07.925
And lonely.

16:09.343 --> 16:13.097
Sometimes, I'd get so excited
just to see another person,

16:14.223 --> 16:16.225
that I'd forget that they could be bad.

16:18.060 --> 16:19.645
I just wanted a friend.

16:20.521 --> 16:21.438
Any friend.

16:22.106 --> 16:25.234
-Jepp is my friend.
-Has he said he's your friend?

16:25.859 --> 16:28.237
No, but he doesn't need to.

16:31.657 --> 16:33.033
Do you want to know the truth?

16:35.536 --> 16:38.455
He's one of the bad people
your father told you about.

16:39.832 --> 16:41.417
He's a Last Man,

16:41.500 --> 16:43.752
the same men who caught you at the Market.

16:44.420 --> 16:46.171
The same men who killed my family.

16:46.880 --> 16:50.592
There's only one reason they'd keep
a hybrid around. It's not to be friends.

16:53.053 --> 16:56.598
The Last Men have made it
their mission to eliminate hybrids.

16:57.182 --> 16:59.393
But we've made it ours to protect them.

17:00.394 --> 17:04.231
That's why you should stay here with us,
not with Jepperd.

17:07.151 --> 17:08.152
Where is he?

17:08.694 --> 17:09.778
I want to see him.

17:10.988 --> 17:13.282
[tense music builds]

17:13.365 --> 17:15.034
-[clock ticking]
-[squelching]

17:15.117 --> 17:16.702
[Dr. Singh inhales sharply]

17:20.456 --> 17:22.499
-[animal chirping]
-[metal clinking]

17:22.583 --> 17:25.085
[alarm clock buzzing]

17:41.602 --> 17:43.270
-[Dr. Singh] Can't sleep?
-Mm.

17:44.146 --> 17:46.940
The pleasures of living
with an incurable disease.

17:47.733 --> 17:49.693
And I wanted to see you off this morning.

17:50.819 --> 17:53.113
Make sure I didn't chicken out?

17:53.197 --> 17:55.157
Make sure you didn't
forget your breakfast.

17:56.075 --> 17:58.077
-[gasps] Oh, my God.
-[Rani chuckles]

17:59.953 --> 18:01.663
Where did you find Pop-Tarts?

18:01.747 --> 18:03.165
[Rani] I talked to Twyla and Harley.

18:03.248 --> 18:05.667
They put in a special order
on their last supply run.

18:05.751 --> 18:07.795
-Thought you could use a pick-me-up.
-Yeah.

18:10.881 --> 18:12.508
Too early for Pop-Tarts?

18:14.093 --> 18:16.720
I… I know the injections aren't working,

18:16.804 --> 18:19.306
and I know we both agreed
after the party at Doug's,

18:19.389 --> 18:23.519
but if I had just another month,
I know… I know I could crack it.

18:23.602 --> 18:24.436
Adi.

18:25.646 --> 18:27.356
We've already been over this.

18:28.941 --> 18:31.026
Dr. Bell's notes were unequivocal.

18:32.945 --> 18:33.904
We need…

18:35.781 --> 18:37.157
a living hybrid.

18:38.158 --> 18:39.118
You're right.

18:40.077 --> 18:41.453
You always are. [snickers]

18:44.164 --> 18:44.998
[sighs]

18:45.707 --> 18:48.043
I hate that you have to do this for me,

18:49.211 --> 18:53.090
that you've always had to sacrifice
something in order to take care of me.

18:55.050 --> 18:57.761
I wish it were any other way,
I… I always have.

18:57.845 --> 18:59.471
-I wouldn't want you to do--
-Hey, hey, hey.

19:00.055 --> 19:00.889
Hey.

19:02.724 --> 19:03.600
I know.

19:05.477 --> 19:07.479
[somber music playing]

19:14.862 --> 19:16.738
[Nancie] Gardener's been slacking, eh?

19:16.822 --> 19:18.615
Oh. Ah.

19:18.699 --> 19:19.616
Hi, Nancie.

19:20.159 --> 19:21.160
Ha.

19:22.369 --> 19:23.287
Good catch.

19:30.794 --> 19:34.840
We must be vigilant with those
little devils. Wouldn't want anyone

19:34.923 --> 19:38.635
thinking the Sick was around,
especially after what happened at Doug's.

19:38.719 --> 19:40.220
[horse nickering]

19:40.304 --> 19:41.805
They pop up from time to time.

19:42.848 --> 19:43.765
They do, at that.

19:44.766 --> 19:45.893
Is, um…

19:46.393 --> 19:49.188
Rani around?
I've been meaning to talk to her.

19:51.356 --> 19:52.399
She's sleeping in.

19:52.482 --> 19:54.568
Ooh, that's unlike her.

19:54.651 --> 19:56.195
Hope she's feeling okay.

19:57.946 --> 20:00.199
It was actually our wedding anniversary,

20:00.282 --> 20:04.244
and we cracked an old Merlot
we've been holding onto for over a decade.

20:05.579 --> 20:06.997
She drank a little too much.

20:07.080 --> 20:10.167
Well, it's important
to celebrate where we can.

20:13.921 --> 20:14.922
Good day, Nancie.

20:18.550 --> 20:20.552
[ominous music playing]

20:27.017 --> 20:30.687
[horse trotting]

20:39.363 --> 20:41.365
[spraying]

20:54.962 --> 20:56.046
[horse snorts]

21:09.768 --> 21:11.019
[door chimes]

21:42.884 --> 21:46.930
[Dr. Bell] Unique secretions from
the pineal gland of a living hybrid,

21:47.014 --> 21:50.851
in specific combination
with hybrid bone marrow stem cells,

21:50.934 --> 21:53.729
form "the secret sauce," as it were,

21:53.812 --> 21:56.648
of our current antiviral treatment.

22:38.815 --> 22:39.775
[gunshot]

22:39.858 --> 22:41.610
[fizzing]

22:41.693 --> 22:43.862
-[explosion]
-[horse neighing]

22:44.780 --> 22:46.782
[neighing continues]

22:46.865 --> 22:49.076
[sinister music climaxes]

23:19.815 --> 23:22.401
[Rani] Look, I'm not sure
what asking him would really do.

23:22.484 --> 23:24.319
[Nancie] I'm just saying
it's worth mentioning,

23:24.403 --> 23:26.029
especially after recent events.

23:26.113 --> 23:28.407
I mean, we really
don't know who among us--

23:28.490 --> 23:29.324
[Dr. Singh] Nancie.

23:30.117 --> 23:30.992
Doctor.

23:31.576 --> 23:35.288
-Nancie just stopped by to--
-That's all right, dear. I'm just leaving.

23:35.372 --> 23:40.043
No, no, no, please, it sounds like
I walked in on an intriguing conversation.

23:41.420 --> 23:43.588
Well, it's just…

23:45.882 --> 23:46.800
Recent events…

23:46.883 --> 23:48.468
She means Doug Duncan.

23:48.552 --> 23:49.469
[Nancie] Rest his soul.

23:49.553 --> 23:53.640
I… I really did want this
to come from you, dear.

23:55.684 --> 23:56.601
[titters]

23:56.685 --> 24:00.480
She thinks we should institute
mandatory weekly virus screenings,

24:00.564 --> 24:02.274
sometimes random too.

24:03.233 --> 24:06.194
-That won't be necessary.
-You seem awfully sure.

24:06.278 --> 24:10.949
Think we have enough test kits for that?
No, uh, we test when we see symptoms.

24:12.033 --> 24:13.326
We all voted.

24:13.410 --> 24:16.746
There have been
three cases in the past six months.

24:17.831 --> 24:18.832
It's a new wave.

24:19.749 --> 24:21.585
We barely survived the last one.

24:21.668 --> 24:22.627
The answer's no.

24:23.837 --> 24:25.130
Well, I'm calling a meeting.

24:25.213 --> 24:27.632
-Maybe it's time we voted again.
-Nancie, please.

24:27.716 --> 24:28.717
I'm sorry.

24:29.509 --> 24:30.927
Let's agree to disagree.

24:31.011 --> 24:34.139
I guess the, uh, community will decide.

24:34.222 --> 24:35.056
[Nancie] Yes.

24:35.891 --> 24:37.851
And we haven't made a wrong turn yet.

24:38.768 --> 24:39.686
I mean…

24:41.646 --> 24:44.149
We're all still alive, aren't we?

24:44.232 --> 24:45.275
[Dr. Singh] Please.

24:52.073 --> 24:53.992
Oh, I almost forgot.

24:54.576 --> 24:56.369
Happy anniversary, Rani.

24:56.995 --> 24:58.038
What's that? Um…

24:58.121 --> 25:00.665
[ominous music playing]

25:01.249 --> 25:02.584
Your anniversary?

25:03.460 --> 25:04.878
It was yesterday, right?

25:05.587 --> 25:06.546
Uh.. [titters]

25:06.630 --> 25:08.215
Right. Um, sorry.

25:08.298 --> 25:11.593
My mind's been all over the place
since the thing with Doug.

25:13.929 --> 25:15.180
I can imagine.

25:18.683 --> 25:20.352
[door clicks]

25:20.977 --> 25:23.647
[woman on radio]
It's dying. It barely eats.

25:23.730 --> 25:25.524
We can't keep hiding it.

25:25.607 --> 25:29.653
We need to keep moving but if the Last Men
see this hybrid thing, we're dead.

25:29.736 --> 25:31.613
Please, anyone, we don't know what--

25:31.696 --> 25:32.906
[radio interference]

25:36.117 --> 25:38.620
Do I need to take
your radio privileges away?

25:40.121 --> 25:41.206
What did I say?

25:42.165 --> 25:44.876
-It's only for listening.
-It's only for listening.

25:45.669 --> 25:47.254
Never talking.

25:47.337 --> 25:48.547
I know.

25:48.630 --> 25:50.674
[Aimee] I know how curious you are.

25:51.550 --> 25:54.135
But there's enough
to explore around here without…

25:55.053 --> 25:56.179
asking for trouble.

25:57.847 --> 25:58.890
Okay.

26:00.517 --> 26:01.393
Come on.

26:03.436 --> 26:04.646
[Aimee chuckles]

26:05.855 --> 26:08.608
["We're All Young Together"
by Walter Martin playing]

26:16.324 --> 26:18.326
-I love it.
-[chuckles] Thanks, Mom.

26:19.327 --> 26:21.663
By the way,
we've been missing a lot of carrots.

26:21.746 --> 26:23.373
-Have you been sneaking them?
-No.

26:23.999 --> 26:26.960
"Garden's not for playing,
it's for working."

26:27.669 --> 26:28.837
All right, Pigtail.

26:29.379 --> 26:31.006
Go get cleaned up for dinner.

26:32.591 --> 26:35.719
♪ We like to sing
This song in harmony… ♪

26:35.802 --> 26:36.928
Three dashes.

26:37.012 --> 26:39.014
♪ And her momma sings too ♪

26:40.098 --> 26:42.559
♪ And the old man taps his shoe… ♪

26:42.642 --> 26:43.643
Needs more.

26:44.436 --> 26:45.645
No, it doesn't.

26:47.063 --> 26:49.024
Mom, look at my nose.

26:49.107 --> 26:51.860
Now look at your nose.
I think I know what I'm talking about.

26:53.653 --> 26:56.114
[Pigtail giggles]

26:56.197 --> 26:58.491
♪ We're all young together… ♪

26:58.575 --> 27:02.704
[on TV] I have prepared
a new plan for Animal Farm.

27:03.204 --> 27:04.122
You know what?

27:04.205 --> 27:05.165
What?

27:05.248 --> 27:06.958
I think it needed more salt.

27:07.584 --> 27:08.627
Unbelievable.

27:09.085 --> 27:10.086
[Aimee chuckles]

27:12.589 --> 27:14.466
I'm gonna go get started on the pump.

27:15.425 --> 27:17.469
You clean up here when you're done.

27:17.552 --> 27:18.762
[indistinct TV chatter]

27:45.914 --> 27:49.042
[bells jingling]

27:51.920 --> 27:52.837
[whispers] Intruder.

27:52.921 --> 27:54.464
[ominous music playing]

28:00.178 --> 28:01.304
[gun cocking]

28:01.846 --> 28:03.098
Just stay close.

28:06.643 --> 28:07.560
Come on.

28:19.656 --> 28:21.741
[gate creaking]

28:39.718 --> 28:40.760
Stay close.

28:41.886 --> 28:43.179
[clattering]

28:45.223 --> 28:46.808
[Aimee] Come. Come on.

28:46.891 --> 28:48.852
[Aimee breathing heavily]

28:52.439 --> 28:53.314
There.

28:53.398 --> 28:55.316
-[leaves rustling]
-Halt!

28:55.400 --> 28:56.401
No, no, no! No!

28:56.484 --> 28:58.528
He's my friend. His name is Bobby.

28:59.446 --> 29:02.407
-[leaves rustling]
-[Bobby moans]

29:04.784 --> 29:08.413
[snuffles]

29:09.330 --> 29:10.498
[Pigtail] He's like me.

29:12.751 --> 29:14.794
Am Bobby.

29:18.590 --> 29:20.008
[Pigtail] Can we keep him?

29:22.469 --> 29:23.303
Please?

29:24.137 --> 29:25.680
They need our help.

29:31.561 --> 29:33.563
[birds squawking]

29:35.899 --> 29:37.275
He's here?

29:37.358 --> 29:38.485
[Bear] Open the door.

29:38.568 --> 29:40.570
[shutter creaking]

29:46.868 --> 29:47.702
Big Man?

29:52.499 --> 29:53.333
Hey, kid.

29:54.542 --> 29:55.960
[Gus] What did they do to you?

29:56.461 --> 29:58.463
Why don't you ask your new friend?

29:59.088 --> 30:01.591
Why don't you tell Gus the truth
about who you really are?

30:01.674 --> 30:02.509
[Jepperd] Aw.

30:03.426 --> 30:04.344
That's sweet.

30:05.470 --> 30:07.430
I didn't take you for a football fan.

30:07.514 --> 30:10.016
-[taser buzzes]
-[Jepperd yelps]

30:10.099 --> 30:11.935
[panting]

30:17.398 --> 30:18.733
Let us go now…

30:20.318 --> 30:24.113
and I might let some of you live
when I get free.

30:24.614 --> 30:26.866
Gus can go anytime he wants.

30:26.950 --> 30:28.201
The rest is up to me.

30:28.284 --> 30:29.577
She's the leader.

30:29.661 --> 30:31.788
Yeah, I got that.

30:44.092 --> 30:46.344
Why don't you tell him about this?

30:51.391 --> 30:52.559
[Jepperd] You got me.

30:53.309 --> 30:55.770
I was a Last Man.

30:57.021 --> 30:58.314
I'm not anymore.

30:59.274 --> 31:00.483
People change.

31:01.317 --> 31:02.193
Happy?

31:02.694 --> 31:04.028
Not even a little.

31:04.112 --> 31:06.781
You were like
one of those guys at the Market?

31:08.408 --> 31:10.827
-Why didn't you tell me?
-Ain't that simple, kid.

31:13.997 --> 31:16.749
Do you even understand
what it was like when the Sick came?

31:17.333 --> 31:18.626
How old were you?

31:18.710 --> 31:19.544
Five?

31:21.170 --> 31:23.798
The world as we knew it was over.

31:23.882 --> 31:27.552
We had to choose a team,
either kill or be killed.

31:28.428 --> 31:31.097
Maybe you'll understand when you grow up.

31:31.806 --> 31:33.766
How many families have you torn apart?

31:35.935 --> 31:38.438
How many children
have you stolen from their parents?

31:39.230 --> 31:41.691
How many kids like Gus
have you made disappear?

31:42.775 --> 31:45.278
You didn't do it because
your back was against the wall.

31:45.361 --> 31:46.946
You did it because you were good at it.

31:47.614 --> 31:50.074
Because underneath it all,
you were broken.

31:54.662 --> 31:56.372
You still are broken.

32:01.210 --> 32:02.337
[Bear] I'm sorry, Gus.

32:03.713 --> 32:04.839
You've hurt people too.

32:08.426 --> 32:10.261
-What?
-Those men on the horses.

32:10.345 --> 32:11.220
You hurt them.

32:11.304 --> 32:13.056
But he's not like them.

32:13.139 --> 32:16.434
He made me a costume
so people would like me,

32:16.517 --> 32:18.686
and he bought me things
he thought I'd like.

32:19.395 --> 32:21.606
And he wakes me up
when I'm having bad dreams.

32:22.523 --> 32:26.069
And he never tried to sell me.
He tried to help me.

32:26.653 --> 32:29.906
He might not be very good at it,
but… at least he tried.

32:29.989 --> 32:30.907
[Jepperd] Kid.

32:31.658 --> 32:33.660
Didn't you hear what she said?

32:34.243 --> 32:35.954
It's okay, you're Big Man.

32:36.037 --> 32:38.831
Look, man, I'm fine.
I can take care of myself.

32:40.541 --> 32:41.834
I always have.

32:43.002 --> 32:47.090
But you need to get out of here
while you can.

32:48.132 --> 32:49.592
Go find your mom.

32:57.308 --> 32:58.601
Ah, kid…

33:02.313 --> 33:03.439
Take him away.

33:03.523 --> 33:04.941
[Gus] No, don't!

33:05.024 --> 33:07.318
Don't hurt him!
Please, don't take him away! No!

33:07.402 --> 33:08.903
-[Rhino] Gus, stand back.
-No!

33:08.987 --> 33:11.239
No! Don't kill him! No!

33:11.322 --> 33:12.365
No!

33:12.448 --> 33:14.325
[somber music playing]

33:15.159 --> 33:17.578
You made a cross-your-heart promise!

33:20.790 --> 33:22.625
[sinister music builds]

33:22.709 --> 33:25.628
[crowd clamoring]

33:29.716 --> 33:31.050
[clamoring fades]

33:36.681 --> 33:39.600
[clattering]

33:42.562 --> 33:44.105
[creature growling]

33:45.815 --> 33:47.483
When you joined this army…

33:49.027 --> 33:49.986
this family…

33:51.362 --> 33:54.782
you made a pledge
as you painted your animal on the wall.

33:55.366 --> 33:57.368
You would defend hybrids

33:58.453 --> 33:59.871
against any harm,

34:00.538 --> 34:01.789
at any cost.

34:04.751 --> 34:07.920
Today that cost may seem higher
than it ever has before.

34:20.808 --> 34:21.642
Today,

34:22.727 --> 34:24.979
we're here to put this man to death.

34:25.730 --> 34:27.523
He has done horrible things.

34:28.733 --> 34:30.234
-[chains rattling]
-But so have we all.

34:31.569 --> 34:33.112
So have I.

34:36.115 --> 34:38.993
The worst may be
letting my anger lead you to revenge.

34:41.412 --> 34:43.081
That is not the animal way.

34:44.957 --> 34:46.751
That only makes us more like him.

34:48.044 --> 34:48.961
Like them.

34:51.714 --> 34:55.093
In my anger, I have forgotten my pledge.

34:55.176 --> 34:56.177
Our pledge…

34:57.553 --> 35:00.223
defend hybrids against all harm.

35:02.016 --> 35:06.062
If we kill this man,
we are harming a very special hybrid.

35:09.107 --> 35:10.775
[sword shinking]

35:13.319 --> 35:15.071
There will be no execution.

35:15.154 --> 35:16.697
-[soldier 1] What?
-[crowd clamoring]

35:16.781 --> 35:18.157
[Tiger] Bullshit!

35:19.117 --> 35:21.994
This man is a monster
and he deserves to die.

35:23.162 --> 35:25.498
What about
all the other hybrids he's hurt?

35:25.581 --> 35:26.749
Stand down, Tiger.

35:27.250 --> 35:28.709
He's brainwashed Gus.

35:28.793 --> 35:29.794
-[clattering]
-[growling]

35:29.877 --> 35:33.589
-And now he's brainwashed you too.
-No, I've just changed my mind.

35:33.673 --> 35:37.343
You may have forgotten what
the Animal Army stands for but we haven't.

35:37.426 --> 35:38.344
Animals forever!

35:38.427 --> 35:41.222
[crowd cheering]

35:41.305 --> 35:44.016
Yeah, no more waiting! Release Daisy!

35:45.017 --> 35:47.728
-[Tiger] Get ready.
-Tiger, don't do it!

35:47.812 --> 35:50.982
-[chains rattling]
-[Daisy growling]

35:51.065 --> 35:52.316
Let her loose!

35:52.400 --> 35:56.112
-[Daisy growling, roaring]
-[Rhino] Pull.

35:58.447 --> 35:59.407
[Rhino] I can't hold her!

36:00.783 --> 36:01.617
Come on!

36:01.701 --> 36:04.036
-[Daisy roars]
-[Pony strains]

36:08.624 --> 36:09.709
[Jepperd] Kid, don't!

36:09.792 --> 36:12.336
[Daisy roaring]

36:16.966 --> 36:18.676
Please don't hurt my friend.

36:19.385 --> 36:22.972
[snarls]

36:39.238 --> 36:40.781
[Rhino] Lock it up.

36:41.824 --> 36:43.618
-No!
-[doors slam]

36:43.701 --> 36:45.912
-No, this isn't the way!
-Let her out!

36:45.995 --> 36:48.414
-[Pony] Let her out! Let her out!
-[soldier 2] Get off me!

36:48.497 --> 36:51.667
[crowd clamoring]

36:51.751 --> 36:53.419
[soldier 3] Take his rope!

36:53.502 --> 36:56.088
[clamoring continues]

36:57.590 --> 36:58.716
[Bear] Stand down!

37:00.635 --> 37:02.637
No! No!

37:02.720 --> 37:03.554
Stand down!

37:03.638 --> 37:06.224
Think we overstayed our welcome,
Sweet Tooth.

37:06.974 --> 37:08.226
[Bear] Tiger, call them off!

37:08.726 --> 37:09.852
Call them off!

37:09.936 --> 37:11.896
[crowd shouting]

37:11.979 --> 37:14.565
[Tiger]
If you're with Bear, you're against us!

37:16.567 --> 37:18.486
Let's get the hell out of here.

37:26.535 --> 37:28.537
["Got It In You" by BANNERS playing]

37:30.623 --> 37:32.416
[narrator] Maybe it goes without saying…

37:34.377 --> 37:37.880
but we're looking for family
from the moment we're born.

37:39.674 --> 37:40.549
Turns out,

37:42.051 --> 37:45.012
we just never know
where we're going to find it.

37:45.721 --> 37:51.060
♪ When the lights go out
And leave you standing in the dark ♪

37:53.312 --> 37:57.942
♪ No one ever told you
This would be so hard ♪

37:59.652 --> 38:03.781
♪ I know you think
Your fire is burning out ♪

38:03.864 --> 38:08.869
♪ But I still see you shining through ♪

38:12.123 --> 38:15.626
♪ You got it in you… ♪

38:15.710 --> 38:18.004
[narrator] And sometimes
our families end up looking

38:18.087 --> 38:20.589
nothing like we thought they would.

38:21.215 --> 38:25.261
And tell everyone you know.
They're all welcome at the Preserve.

38:25.845 --> 38:27.305
[narrator] And sometimes,

38:27.388 --> 38:29.640
we do things for family that we…

38:30.558 --> 38:32.351
That we never thought we could.

38:32.435 --> 38:33.436
[Dr. Singh] Nancie, wait!

38:33.519 --> 38:35.938
-It's not what you think!
-I knew you guys were lying.

38:36.022 --> 38:38.816
You've been acting suspicious
for weeks, and Rani looks awful.

38:38.899 --> 38:42.737
I could tell at the party, but then
when Doug's finger started twitching, I--

38:42.820 --> 38:46.699
You don't understand, I have something,
something that can maybe help all of us.

38:46.782 --> 38:48.326
You are a liar!

38:48.409 --> 38:49.994
We have to burn everything!

38:50.077 --> 38:52.496
-Calm down!
-I have to get the others! Don't touch me!

38:52.580 --> 38:53.956
-[horse neighing]
-Nancie!

38:54.040 --> 38:56.167
[ominous music playing]

39:03.257 --> 39:04.258
Oh, God.

39:08.012 --> 39:08.929
Oh, God.

39:13.559 --> 39:14.977
[Dr. Singh] She's not breathing.

39:15.061 --> 39:17.563
[panting]

39:19.190 --> 39:21.484
[narrator]
Because family is always worth it.

39:22.485 --> 39:23.486
Come on.

39:27.990 --> 39:29.700
[Dr. Singh] Okay, come on. One, two…

39:45.424 --> 39:46.384
[narrator] At least…

39:48.302 --> 39:50.137
well, we sure as hell hope so.

39:51.889 --> 39:56.018
[ominous music climaxes]

39:58.771 --> 40:02.691
[journey music playing]
